{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e3c47a45-2ea3-4b35-8b8f-2a7b5acb7c13",
    "name": "Hiveboard Task 13 - Notes and Decisions Verification",
    "description": "Postman collection for manually verifying Task 13 acceptance criteria from IMPLEMENTATION-GUIDE.md.\n\nRecommended setup:\n1. Start the API in Development mode so the dev seeder can create the default organization and worker agents.\n2. Set HIVEBOARD_ADMIN_KEY before starting the API so it matches the adminApiKey collection variable.\n3. If your local DB is not freshly seeded, update worker1ApiKey and worker2ApiKey to valid active agent keys in the same organization.\n\nThe collection creates an isolated project and task for each run, then verifies:\n- workers and the coordinator can add task notes\n- note responses include author metadata\n- note_added task events are recorded\n- decisions can be created as task-linked and standalone records\n- markdown content is preserved\n- project decision listing and filtering work as expected",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
